.TH POWER-PROFILE-CTL 1 "December 2025" "Power Profile Manager 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
power-profile-ctl \- Control and monitor power profile manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B power-profile-ctl
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B power-profile-ctl
is a command-line utility to monitor and control the power profile manager daemon.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show current power profile status including battery level, power status, active profile,
and CPU settings. This is the default command if none is specified.
.TP
.B monitor
Live monitoring of power profile with automatic refresh every 2 seconds.
Press Ctrl+C to stop monitoring.
.TP
.B config
Display the current configuration from /etc/power-profiled.conf
.TP
.B help
Show help message with available commands
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show current status:
.B power-profile-ctl status
.TP
Monitor in real-time:
.B power-profile-ctl monitor
.TP
View configuration:
.B power-profile-ctl config
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/power-profiled.conf
Configuration file
.TP
.I /var/run/power-profile-state
Current profile state
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR power-profiled (8),
.BR tlp (8)
